asked me in a comment if I had a timeline of my fitness journey and I didn’t. So I took the time to do one for all you who follow me and support me. 

Now I try to be as transparent as possible when it comes down to my fitness. This week alone I’ve been getting so many backlash about how I didn’t lose this naturally and how it was impossible. So many disgusting comments and people writing to me in my DM saying that I’m a FRAUD”! I don’t know what makes people think that I am or have them the idea.

Yes I was wearing disposable garments that appear to be the ones people wear when under going surgeries, I had no idea. I went to get a sauna session. Some people said that I wasn’t truthful with my results, nobody here knows me like that personally besides my family and close friends. Y’all decided to follow me because you see some REAL RESULTS! I never faked anything. I’m a real genuine person with a great heart and care for people. 

I tried my best to make this video for those who are losing hope and are struggling forreal.  Get DMs about people who are not mentally in the right state of mind, depressed.

You may not know but I was depressed when I started. I was down I was sad I didn’t love myself, I wanted to eliminate myself from this world. I tried, but my God my Lord and Savior gave me strength and I prayed every day to Him crying to help me. 

I didn’t feel good about myself at all I was the biggest one in my family. Nobody in my family is fat or big. It doesn’t even run in our family. When I gained weight I was in a very tough spot. I was in a relationship that was mentally & emotionally abusive. I was drinking my life away I became an alcoholic and drank my feelings away and the pain I ensured. 

I would go to stores to try things in in H&M and they didn’t fit. I had holes in my pants cause my thighs rubbed together. I was disgusted with myself cause I’d how let myself go so carelessly. Then to hear people say here that I had SURGERY is sooo freaking misleading and absurd.

My story is long, so long I could write a book about it. (One day)

This video represents me! 

I hope I gave you some hope ❤️

👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
The team at @bodysmartfitness want you to know the truth about diets, nutrition, food, fitness and the mindset hacks that will ensure your success. 
 
😀 We all want to feel good. 
 
😀 We all want to feel happy. 
 
⭐️ We all want to be a success (however success looks for us). 
 
@Bodysmartfitness blend a powerful trilogy of mindset, nutrition and fitness education to help people stop being stuck in a yo-yo cycle of fads and frustration. 
 
🌎 Founded by Jaymie Moran and with a global team of online coaches in the UK, America and Australia, the team coach women to get sustainable results for life without giving up the foods they love. 
 
💬 Jaymie said, "We wanted to start the Body Smart Fitness YouTube channel to give even more people the right science-backed information, inspiration and tools to create lasting results. Basically, we want to give you the TRUTH." 
 
💬 "Nothing gets me more annoyed and frustrated than people remaining stuck in a trap of yo-yo diets and ineffective exercise for years, coupled with a mindset that has been shaped by you thinking you're a failure every time you try and fail a diet. You're not a failure, you have been lied to." 
 
😥 "The diet industry keeps you trapped. My team and I are here to help you break free from that trap." 
 
💪 "Because losing weight is the easy part." 
 
🤯 "It is keeping it off that is hard." 
 
👉 Access @bodysmartfitness YouTube channel via the link in bio. Don't forget to subscribe and click the notification bell so you get first access to the videos.

To get rid of fat deposits on your back, you’ll need to start by creating a caloric deficit. That means that you’ll need to burn more calories during the day than you consume.

In addition to cutting calories, you’ll get rid of back fat more quickly if you focus your exercise routine to target the muscles in your upper and lower back.

Adding high-intensity interval exercise (HIIT) to your routine, along with working out these specific muscles, will start to give you the results that you’re looking for.

#quarentreino em casa tbm da pra chorar 😅💪🏽 ·

1- Agachamento peso corporal 
Realizar 3x series dessa sequência c/ 30seg descanso por série 
30rep completas +
30rep curtas +
30seg isometria 
2- 3x series dessa sequência - 30 seg descanso por série 
Afundo +Agachamento+ Isometria- A cada passada para cada lado (total de 10 para cada perna) realiza 5 agachamentos em movimento acelerado , no final , 1 min de isometria ( costas na parede)

3- Agachamento Búlgaro ( pés apoiado na cadeira/ banco/ sofá ) 4x15rep cada lado sem descanso 
4- Elevação de quadril unilateral ( tronco apoiado na cadeira/banco/ sofá) 4x20rep cada lado sem descanso 
5 - 4 apoios ( realizar os movimentos cadência lenta ) 3xseries para cada lado - 10seg de descanso ao final de cada série 
15 rep - joelhos em extensão .+
15rep - joelhos flexionados 
6- Panturrilhas ( utilizar um degrau ou apoio)
5x30seg de execução ( total amplitude ) - 15 seg descanso
.

Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
Before eating vs. after eating! 
•
•
Hi babiesssss💕 I’m posting this because I’m constantly getting messages about gaining weight/building glutes etc....and how eating more just makes them have a big belly. I’m sure you know by now....that you do have to increase how much you eat in order to gain weight. Unfortunately, not everyone gets to see behind the sides. I have had so many conversations with clients and others explaining that 1) it’s okay if your belly gets bigger after eating 2) it literally happens to EVERY SINGLE PERSON. 
•
•
Social media allows us to share what we want and keep other things behind closed doors. Nonetheless, I’m here to say that I don’t walk around with a flat tummy or look cut 24/7....more often than not, I have a food baby lol it’s the process of any weight gain journey. You’re not going to walk around with a 6-pack all the time. And that’s normal! I know it can be discouraging at times but that doesn’t mean you’re not progressing✨💕 so don’t worry sunshine! By @destinykayla_

Cellulite to PEACHY SELFIE (aka ‘belfie*’) in 10 seconds flat?

Oooor just another reason to remember the internet is curated and you’re doing great.

Here’s how I did it:

🍑 Popped my bum on the counter. What’s closest to the mirror/camera looks biggest. It also pulls my skin taunt so hides my CELLULITE.

🍑 Gave myself a WEDGIE. This creates definition in the bum cheeks so bum looks bigger.

🍑 Used my hand to hide my SKIN FOLDS.

🍑 Arched my back, played with angles.

🍑 Squeezed my back bum cheek.

🍑 Stopped breathing.

And BAM there we go. The perfect insta-ready belfie.

But (or butt?! 😂) here’s the thing: over 80% of women have cellulite.

Some studies say over 90%.

It’s super common. Even if we don’t see it on here. Even if it’s so easy to pose, edit, or hide away.

So remember online isn’t real.

And you’re amazing.
(via @danaemercer)

👉 Double tap if you agree! Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips. 👉 follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
🍽 Anyone can work out for an hour but controlling what goes on your plate the other 23 hours of the day is the hard part. 
 
😢 "We coach so many women who come to us thinking carbs are bad or they have to do exercise as punishment for what they ate." says Jaymie Moran from @bodysmartfitness 
 
🍵 "Many people think they need a teatox, detox, diet shake or pill to get results but it doesn't have to be that way!" 
 
😢 "When you try and 'control' what is on your plate it's made so much harder when you have food rules, a poor relationship with food or you have restricted foods too often." 
 
🍎"Breaking out of that cycle and the yo-yo results that are so frustrating for people is the first step. It starts with two key things; your education around nutrition and your mindset that shapes how you think which drives your behaviour which influences your actions." 🧠 
 
👩‍🎓 "My advice is always to learn about calories and what a calorie deficit is. We work hard at @bodysmartfitness to provide this powerful education for free to anyone who follows us." 
 
🤔 "Next work on yourself. What makes you turn to food? What makes you give up? What excuses and limiting beliefs hold you back from success?" 
 
👯‍♀️"If you can't figure out these answers, that's where 1:1 tailored coaching can help." 
 
🗣 "At @bodysmartfitness, We believe that the diet industry has to change and our hashtag #CutTheBS exists so we can help people cut through the BS on social media and the diets that keep people stuck." 
 
🧠 "We also work with clients on our non-judgemental and compassionate coaching that helps them #CutTheBS with themselves; their limiting beliefs, their excuses and their self-talk that has been holding them back not just with fat loss but their confidence in general."

The angle you see VS the one you don’t (with Koala kitten as a bonus) / or let’s talk BOYFRIENDS.

In the last six months, I’ve been DMed multiple times by gals telling me they’ve shown their partner my photos.

‘And he thought it wasn’t the SAME PERSON!’ They add.

A friend of mine used her body to demonstrate. ‘Look at what happens when I relax. Look at my skin.’ Her partner had never seen her sit like that before.

She hadn’t allowed herself to around him.

I’ve had one man, a husband, message me something similar. He always thought only the women in his life had CELLULITE sitting down.

‘I never saw it on social,’ he added. So clearly it was just the gals he knew that had these, to use his words, ‘imperfections.’ The offline women were ‘off’. The online women perfect.

This is a theme we are seeing more and more. Young boys are growing up with dark internet corners and ideal social media worlds. By 10, studies show they’ll have been exposed to plenty of not-for-children content. TikTok slips in face editing apps automatically. There are video tools that change bodies real time.

All this brings me back to my first point:
Let’s talk about guys.

And how we can make a change.

I don’t know the answer to this one.
I don’t have any advice.
But it’s on my mind and it’s in my DMs.
And at this exact moment, it’s bouncing around the comment section of an old post too.

But perhaps a first step would be this: Let your partner see you from all the angles,
And remind the kiddos that online isn’t real.

Before we get to a point where only glossy perfection is the only type of reality so many of us know.⁣⁣⁣️️️⁣⁣️️️️️️️️️️️️
